This paper deals with privacy violations in web browsing, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of advanced machine learning techniques to analyze microarchitectural footprints suggests a focus on data analysis and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed mitigation strategies involve software design and implementation, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE). The use of hardware performance events suggests a focus on computer architecture and design (cs.DC). Finally, the potential impact on user privacy suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
